2026-04-20T05:46:51.228Z JOY-00F8-F2 item.updated "Implement joy ai rotate per ADR-033" [ai:claude@joy delegated-by:horst.schwarz@joydev.com]
2026-04-20T05:47:21.733Z JOY-00F8-F2 comment.added "Plan: Implement 'joy ai rotate <ai-member>' per ADR-033.\n\nSubcommand lives under 'joy ai rotate' next to existing init/update/reset. Requires ManageProject capability (same as token add).\n\nFlow:\n1. Authenticate acting human (passphrase, same pattern as token add).\n2. Verify <ai-member> is registered and has an ai_delegations entry under the acting human. If no entry: bail with 'no delegation to rotate, run joy auth token add first' (this is the (None pub, None priv) bootstrap case).\n3. Generate fresh Ed25519 keypair.\n4. Write new private to ~/.local/state/joy/delegations/<project>/<ai>.key (mode 0600, overwriting any existing file -> covers (Some,None), (Some,Some mismatch), (Some,Some match) uniformly).\n5. Update project.yaml: members[<human>].ai_delegations[<ai>].delegation_key = new_pub; rotated = now. Single write via write_yaml_preserve.\n6. Single commit via auto_git_add.\n7. Print: 'Rotated delegation for <ai>. Prior tokens and sessions are invalidated. Issue a fresh token with joy auth token add <ai>.'\n\nError-message rework in auth.rs:\n- Fall 1 (Some,Some mismatch, Z. 534): 'Delegation state for X is inconsistent (local private key does not match the public key in project.yaml). Run joy ai rotate X to replace the keypair with a fresh one. Prior tokens are invalidated.'\n- Fall 2 (Some,None, Z. 548): 'Local delegation private key for X is missing on this machine. Run joy ai rotate X to generate a fresh pair. Note: this invalidates any prior tokens and any copy of the key on other machines.'\n- Fall 3 (None,Some, Z. 554): no mention of rotate - this is a manual-resolution case. 'Local delegation key for X exists but project.yaml has no entry. Remove the orphan key at <path> and re-run joy auth token add, or investigate why the yaml entry is missing.'\n\nTests:\n- Unit tests for any new helpers.\n- Integration bats tests: rotate succeeds on working delegation (new key on disk, new public in yaml, rotated set, old token fails project_id/delegation_key check); rotate from (Some,None) state; rotate errors when no ai_delegations entry exists.\n\nPreserves ADR-033 invariants:\n- One write per (human,AI) pair at rotation events only - no new project.yaml write surface.\n- Single commit, stable BTreeMap ordering - no merge conflict surface added.\n- delegation_key, created, rotated fields already exist in AiDelegationEntry, no model change needed." [ai:claude@joy delegated-by:horst.schwarz@joydev.com]
